    public interface AmpFMConfigurable
    Interface for accessing the AMP Feature Manager settings. All AMP interface controls implement this interface. This gives access to the FM name of each control and its type. By using these two methods, it is possible to identify any FM state for any component. For example for the project title, you will have getFMName() equal to the 'Project Title' and the getFMType() to AmpFMTypes#FIELD If the feature manager database is queried using these two values it will say if the project title is visible - Component.isVisible() and enabled Component.isEnabled()
    See Also:
    AmpFMTypes, FMUtil, AmpComponentPanel
